A man is being treated for life-threatening injuries after a vehicle was found on its roof, Devon and Cornwall Police say. The single-vehicle crash happened on the B3233 in Bideford at about 04:40 BST on Sunday. A 41-year-old man was taken to hospital and remained there while he received treatment, officers said.Police said they were appealing for any witnesses who may have seen a blue BMW 120 in the Barnstaple or Bideford areas shortly before the crash.
